android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.MOUNT_UNMOUNT_FILESYS.description: Allows the application to mount and unmount file systems for removable storage.

android.permission.GET_TASKS.description: Allows application to retrieve information about currently and recently running tasks. May allow malicious applications to discover private information about other applications.

android.permission.SYSTEM_ALERT_WINDOW.description: Allows an application to show system-alert windows. Malicious applications can take over the entire screen of the phone.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.SET_WALLPAPER.description: Allows the application to set the system wallpaper.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.FLASHLIGHT.description: Allows the application to control the flashlight.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.mc.browser.activity.BrowserActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

playstore_details.title: MC Browser - privacy and security browser
playstore_details.description:
☆ lightweight and practical: ultra-small installation package, only 6 MB, less memory occupied, 0 seconds to start!
☆ Download acceleration: Intelligent speed up downloading all kinds of files, save time, and save network traffic.
☆ Advertising Blocker: Block all kinds of annoying popups and advertisements to give you a comfortable browsing experience.
☆ Security: Protect your Internet security! Built-in global No1 anti-virus engine (AV-TEST certification)
☆ Incognito Mode for private browsing.



MC Browser is a lightweight mobile browser that protects you from malicious threats and gives you a fast browsing experience! While providing download acceleration features and file management features, this powerful probe download feature of MC Browser makes it easier for you to download favorite files and videos.
In addition, MC Browser also has an effective Adblock function, which can effectively block all kinds of annoying popups and advertisements when you browse the web or shop online, giving you a comfortable browsing experience.
What are you waiting for? Get your hands on the best & fast browser.




Amazing Browser Features:
★ Smart Download
Using intelligent analysis, automatically select the fastest download path, download faster and save traffic.

★ Ad blocking
Adblock function can effectively block all kinds of annoying popups and advertisements and give you a comfortable browsing experience. More importantly, ad blocking will not only increase the speed of web page loading, but also help you save more network data traffic.

★ Prevent fraud
The MC browser promptly alerts the user before the user browses those potentially fraudulent or malicious web pages, and protects the user's network security.

★ Document Management
Easily manage all kinds of files, powerful file management

★ Privacy Mode
No history, cookie information and cache files are left behind after browsing. The privacy mode provides you with a completely confidential browsing experience.

★ Night mode
Use nighttime browsing mode to protect your eyes in low light conditions.

★ Full screen mode
Full screen and non-full screen, you can choose any one.

★ No picture mode
When you don’t want to see the picture, you can open the no-image mode, saving network data traffic and saving time when loading web pages.

★ Screenshot Graffiti
You can edit and scribble arbitrarily after taking a screenshot, or you can add text, pictures, and filter effects after selecting the image.

★ Data Clearance
All historical data can be deleted when you exit the app. When you want to visit some sensitive private websites, MC browser will be your best choice.

★ Speed ??Dial
You can save your favorite URL to your home page for speed dialing.

★ Find page content
Supports page content lookup characters.

★ Font adjustment
Choose your favorite font size

★ Personal bookmarks
Save URLs to bookmarks with one click, and it's easy to manage

★ Switch search engine
A variety of search engines can be switched.

★ multiple Tab Support
Supports browsing multiple web pages at the same time. You can open a new web page in a new tab page or silently open a web page in the background.


---
Contact the developer:
startmoni@foxmail.com
